    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II"
  },
  "hasVerificationActivity": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/mesh-convergence-study",
    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh Convergence and Discretization Error Quantification",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA model using three mesh densities (coarse: ~85k elements, medium: ~220k elements, fine: ~510k elements). Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the discretization error in construct stiffness and yield force QoIs. The grid convergence index (GCI) was computed for each refinement level. Results demonstrated monotonic convergence with GCI values below 1.2% for all QoIs at the medium mesh density, which was subsequently adopted for the validation ensemble. This activity was coordinated across all three modeling teams (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) to ensure consistent mesh quality metrics.",
    "activityType": "MeshRefinementStudy",
    "startedAtTime": "2025-09-10T08:00:00Z",
    "endedAtTime": "2025-10-05T17:00:00Z"
  },
